Diagnosis: Gymnodamaeidae with a ventral plate typically lacking an anogenital bridge ( Figs. 4, 7 , arrows), but with lateral pits; genital plates with smooth median margin and bearing 7 pairs of setae, seta g 2 inserted posteriad g 1 ; 2 pairs of adanal setae. Legs without retrotecta on distal segments (
Fig. 8
), femur IV with 2 setae. Prodorsum without X-shaped raised cerotegumental ridges (
