); pedotectum II rounded distally. Notogaster flattened, with 5 pairs of more or less sessile setae ( h 1-2 , p 1-3 ), raised rim, crenulate outer margin, and posterior median nipple-like process between setae h 1 ; without anterior median tubercular patch; cerotegument with spherical pustules and usually with a pattern of raised ridges or cells and parallel marginal folds (
